the neighboring farm.

492
00:24:19,796 --> 00:24:25,190
It would wipe out the native corn and
take over the other farmer's field.

493
00:24:25,191 --> 00:24:27,421
I was trying to re-engineer the seed

494
00:24:27,422 --> 00:24:31,020
so it could achieve harmony
with the other strains.

495
00:24:31,021 --> 00:24:33,710
But Dafoe ordered me not to.

496
00:24:33,711 --> 00:24:34,811
Why?

497
00:24:34,812 --> 00:24:36,520
At the time, I didn't know it,

498
00:24:36,521 --> 00:24:39,197
but once the gene spread
to the neighboring farms,

499
00:24:39,198 --> 00:24:42,425
Dafoe started suing the
farmers for selling his corn..

500
00:24:42,426 --> 00:24:44,454
My corn.. To the consumer.

501
00:24:44,455 --> 00:24:45,939
On what grounds?

502
00:24:45,940 --> 00:24:48,241
Copyright infringement.

503
00:24:48,242 --> 00:24:50,761
He held the patent on the gene.

504
00:24:50,762 --> 00:24:53,376
He sued them for selling a strain
of corn that blew in on the wind?

505
00:24:53,377 --> 00:24:54,490
Are you kidding me?

506
00:24:54,491 --> 00:24:58,197
Look, they didn't realize
they were growing it.

507
00:24:58,198 --> 00:24:59,551
A lot of them went into foreclosure.

508
00:24:59,552 --> 00:25:01,377
Oh. Of course. Let me guess..

509
00:25:01,378 --> 00:25:03,667
Dafoe started buying up
their farms on the cheap.

510
00:25:03,668 --> 00:25:07,025
I went to Dafoe. I told him
if he doesn't drop the suits,

511
00:25:07,026 --> 00:25:09,096
I would inform the
Department of Agriculture

512
00:25:09,097 --> 00:25:10,179
that he'd planned the whole thing.

513
00:25:10,180 --> 00:25:12,412
Right, and then he offered
you the endowed chair

514
00:25:12,413 --> 00:25:14,883
and maybe a little
grant money as a kicker.

515
00:25:14,884 --> 00:25:17,028
Look you're a scientist.

516
00:25:17,029 --> 00:25:18,735
You know how hard it is to get funding..

517
00:25:18,736 --> 00:25:20,447
Spare me that crap.

518
00:25:20,448 --> 00:25:23,812
You took your 30 pieces of silver,
and those farmers lost everything.

519
00:25:23,813 --> 00:25:24,899
No, you don't understand.

520
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:27,579
No, I think I understand just fine..

521
00:25:27,580 --> 00:25:29,800
Professor.

522
00:25:31,569 --> 00:25:35,829
Kevin Lang, Cal Bowden, Ray Donaldson..

523
00:25:36,725 --> 00:25:39,248
Any of these names mean
anything to you, Mr. Dafoe?

524
00:25:39,249 --> 00:25:40,630
Uh, no, I've never heard of them.

525
00:25:40,631 --> 00:25:43,622
Of course not. You got lawyers for that.

526
00:25:43,623 --> 00:25:46,104
Lang, Bowden, and Donaldson
were three of the farmers

527
00:25:46,105 --> 00:25:48,648
whose lives you ruined
when you sued them

528
00:25:48,649 --> 00:25:52,497
for copyright infringement
for unknowingly taking corn

529
00:25:52,498 --> 00:25:55,358
containing the Dafoe gene to market.

530
00:25:55,359 --> 00:25:57,426
That gene was patented.

531
00:25:57,427 --> 00:26:00,130
Yeah, and designed to obliterate
every cornstalk in its path.

532
00:26:00,131 --> 00:26:01,668
Scantlin handled the lawsuits,

533
00:26:01,669 --> 00:26:04,219
and then Anderson fast-tracked
the farms to foreclosure,

534
00:26:04,220 --> 00:26:07,453
so you could snap up those
properties for pennies on the dollar.

535
00:26:07,454 --> 00:26:09,855
Yes, that's called good business.

536
00:26:09,856 --> 00:26:12,860
U.S. Attorney's gonna call
it conspiracy to commit fraud.

537
00:26:12,861 --> 00:26:14,452
All right, listen, Sweetie,

538
00:26:14,453 --> 00:26:16,938
I'm not gonna say another word
to you without a lawyer present.

539
00:26:16,939 --> 00:26:19,156
That's fine.

540
00:26:19,157 --> 00:26:21,011
But in the meantime..

541
00:26:21,012 --> 00:26:22,340
The killer is still out there.

542
00:26:22,341 --> 00:26:24,814
It's a pretty good bet
that you are on his list.

543
00:26:24,815 --> 00:26:30,715
So I suggest you tell us which of the
farmers you ruined might be doing this.

544
00:26:31,395 --> 00:26:36,503
Okay, there was an incident
at the shareholders meeting.

545
00:26:36,504 --> 00:26:38,589
A very angry man stormed into the room,

546
00:26:38,590 --> 00:26:42,030
yelling threats and obscenities,
and he had to be escorted out.

547
00:26:42,031 --> 00:26:42,867
I need a name.

548
00:26:42,868 --> 00:26:46,241
I don't know. Maybe my security
people might have it. Look..

549
00:26:46,242 --> 00:26:49,504
Are you going to be
able to keep me safe?

550
00:26:49,505 --> 00:26:52,153
Oh, yeah. U.S. Marshals
will protect you.

551
00:26:52,154 --> 00:26:54,815
After all, we wouldn't want
anything happening to you

552
00:26:54,816 --> 00:26:59,436
before you can start
serving your sentence.

553
00:27:02,795 --> 00:27:06,996
Got the name of the farmer that stormed the
shareholder meeting and threatened Dafoe..

554
00:27:06,997 --> 00:27:08,843
Paul Levasseur.

555
00:27:08,844 --> 00:27:10,432
Great. Let's go pick him up.

556
00:27:10,433 --> 00:27:13,421
He's serving 8 to 10
in Stateville Prison.

557
00:27:13,422 --> 00:27:16,662
Been there three months.

558
00:27:16,919 --> 00:27:18,914
Not our guy.

559
00:27:18,915 --> 00:27:21,919
But maybe he can tell us who is.

560
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:23,612
How do you figure that?

561
00:27:23,613 --> 00:27:27,416
Why did the killer put
his message in a newspaper?

562
00:27:27,417 --> 00:27:29,158
Maybe because he was
sending it to somebody whose

563
00:27:29,159 --> 00:27:32,187
letters get opened and read
before they're delivered.

564
00:27:32,188 --> 00:27:35,008
Someone in prison.

565
00:27:36,839 --> 00:27:41,010
My great-great-grandfather
homesteaded that land.

566
00:27:41,011 --> 00:27:43,351
My family..

567
00:27:43,398 --> 00:27:46,010
Farmed it for 100 years.

568
00:27:46,011 --> 00:27:49,018
After the lawsuit, I tried
other things to get by.

569
00:27:49,019 --> 00:27:51,539
Sold tractors.

570
00:27:51,939 --> 00:27:55,419
Dug ditches for the County.

571
00:27:55,901 --> 00:27:57,296
Nothing stuck.

572
00:27:57,297 --> 00:27:59,058
So you robbed a bank.

573
00:27:59,059 --> 00:28:01,891
Just trying to keep
my family above water.

574
00:28:01,892 --> 00:28:05,546
Losing the farm, seeing me behind bars..

575
00:28:05,547 --> 00:28:08,316
Broke my wife's heart.

576
00:28:08,317 --> 00:28:12,157
She hung herself nine weeks ago.

577
00:28:12,172 --> 00:28:14,752
I'm so sorry.

578
00:28:16,063 --> 00:28:21,265
Listen, Mr. Levasseur, we're here
to talk to you about your son, Eddie.

579
00:28:21,266 --> 00:28:22,728
The coded message in the newspaper..

580
00:28:22,729 --> 00:28:27,049
He put that there for you, didn't he?

581
00:28:27,277 --> 00:28:29,554
"Front-page news".

582
00:28:29,555 --> 00:28:32,088
Just like he said.

583
00:28:32,089 --> 00:28:36,631
I tried to call him after
I read about Scantlin.

584
00:28:36,632 --> 00:28:38,086
But his phone was turned off.

585
00:28:38,087 --> 00:28:40,144
You could have called the police.

586
00:28:40,145 --> 00:28:43,685
I know I should have, but..

587
00:28:44,918 --> 00:28:50,143
He was your boy. You
couldn't bear to turn him in.

588
00:28:50,144 --> 00:28:51,431
After..

589
00:28:51,432 --> 00:28:55,360
After this all went down,
something in him broke.

590
00:28:55,361 --> 00:28:59,589
But I swear to you, he's a good boy.

591
00:28:59,590 --> 00:29:00,650
A brilliant boy.

592
00:29:00,651 --> 00:29:03,200
Finished college in three years.

593
00:29:03,201 --> 00:29:05,976
Couldn't wait to get
started in on his PHD.

594
00:29:05,977 --> 00:29:08,091
But he had to drop out
after you lost the farm.

595
00:29:08,092 --> 00:29:10,070
I couldn't send him a dime.

596
00:29:10,071 --> 00:29:14,410
He's been teaching
high-school math in Harvey.

597
00:29:14,411 --> 00:29:16,878
Actually, he hasn't been
there in over a month.

598
00:29:16,879 --> 00:29:19,166
He hasn't been back to
his apartment, either.

599
00:29:19,167 --> 00:29:22,952
We need to find him
before someone else dies.

600
00:29:22,953 --> 00:29:26,973
Do you have any idea where he is?

601
00:29:27,815 --> 00:29:32,515
There's a.. There's a place
he used to like to go to think.

602
00:29:32,516 --> 00:29:36,716
On the back acreage of our old farm.

603
00:29:44,921 --> 00:29:49,181
Look at this. He knew we were coming.

604
00:29:50,539 --> 00:29:52,371
"Hey, kindred, my life's an open book".

605
00:29:52,372 --> 00:29:54,846
"When you crack this one,
you'll know everything".

606
00:29:54,847 --> 00:29:55,972
"But search your mind".

607
00:29:55,973 --> 00:29:58,000
"Do you really want to stop me?"

608
00:29:58,001 --> 00:29:59,004
What is it with this guy?

609
00:29:59,005 --> 00:30:01,277
First he blows you off, then
he leaves you another clue?

610
00:30:01,278 --> 00:30:04,614
He wants to avenge the injustice done
to his Father and the other farmers,

611
00:30:04,615 --> 00:30:06,631
but he did not mean to kill
an innocent college student,

612
00:30:06,632 --> 00:30:09,620
so maybe he's feeling
guilty or conflicted.

613
00:30:09,621 --> 00:30:11,254
Some part of him wants to get caught.

614
00:30:11,255 --> 00:30:12,660
Let's give him what he wants.

615
00:30:12,661 --> 00:30:15,860
"My life's an open book".

616
00:30:15,861 --> 00:30:17,293
"Open book". It's a book cipher.

617
00:30:17,294 --> 00:30:19,455
Look, the numbers are
in groups of three.

618
00:30:19,456 --> 00:30:22,198
The first one corresponds to a
page number in a particular book,

619
00:30:22,199 --> 00:30:25,509
the second one.. Second number
to.. To a line on that page,

620
00:30:25,510 --> 00:30:27,456
and the third number
to a word in that line.

621
00:30:27,457 --> 00:30:29,461
You find the words, you put them
together, you get your message.

622
00:30:29,462 --> 00:30:32,128
- What book?
- It could..

623
00:30:32,129 --> 00:30:36,184
It could be any book in the world.

624
00:30:36,185 --> 00:30:39,905
You're not listening, old boy.

625
00:30:40,282 --> 00:30:42,619
He's telling you
everything you need to know.

626
00:30:42,620 --> 00:30:45,611
What do you mean? What
are you talking about?

627
00:30:45,612 --> 00:30:48,792
I didn't say anything.

628
00:30:49,783 --> 00:30:53,203
"Search your mind," Pierce.

629
00:30:54,410 --> 00:30:56,544
I am. I am.

630
00:30:56,545 --> 00:30:57,567
It's not helping!

631
00:30:57,568 --> 00:30:59,805
Daniel, you all right?

632
00:30:59,806 --> 00:31:01,485
Yeah. Don't.. Don't worry about me.

633
00:31:01,486 --> 00:31:06,047
Okay? I'm f.. Fine.
Just don't worry about..

634
00:31:06,048 --> 00:31:07,848
Me.

635
00:31:08,296 --> 00:31:11,314
You need to take me home.

636
00:31:11,315 --> 00:31:12,327
This is our key.

637
00:31:12,328 --> 00:31:14,401
"The Mind: Knowing The Unknowable".

638
00:31:14,402 --> 00:31:16,214
By Dr. Daniel Pierce. I love this book.

639
00:31:16,215 --> 00:31:19,118
- But what do you..
- He's not saying "search your mind".

640
00:31:19,119 --> 00:31:20,838
He's saying "search your mind".

641
00:31:20,839 --> 00:31:24,776
- He means the title of your book.
- Yeah.

642
00:31:24,777 --> 00:31:26,909
Go to page..

643
00:31:26,910 --> 00:31:28,770
312.

644
00:31:29,353 --> 00:31:32,593
Second line, third word.

645
00:31:33,038 --> 00:31:35,138
"Today".

646
00:31:37,110 --> 00:31:38,807
Page 57.

647
00:31:38,808 --> 00:31:41,868
17th line, 12th word.

648
00:31:52,829 --> 00:31:55,825
14th line, 9th word.

649
00:31:55,826 --> 00:31:57,986
"Family".

650
00:31:59,521 --> 00:32:04,366
"Today I destroy the villain the same
way the villain destroyed my family".

651
00:32:04,367 --> 00:32:07,148
"Destroy the villain".
Who's he talking about?

652
00:32:07,149 --> 00:32:09,148
It's got to be Dafoe. I mean, he's..

653
00:32:09,149 --> 00:32:10,806
He's the main villain in
this whole sordid story.

654
00:32:10,807 --> 00:32:12,208
Dafoe is in protective custody.

655
00:32:12,209 --> 00:32:14,677
How's the killer gonna
destroy him there?

656
00:32:14,678 --> 00:32:18,427
There are a million ways to destroy
someone whose only priority is profits.

657
00:32:18,428 --> 00:32:21,050
I mean, you could take out
their processing plants,

658
00:32:21,051 --> 00:32:24,192
or their warehouses or
their grain elevators.

659
00:32:24,193 --> 00:32:25,633
Yeah, it's a huge company.

660
00:32:25,634 --> 00:32:28,120
We don't have the manpower to
protect every one of his facilities.

661
00:32:28,121 --> 00:32:33,221
But we can try. Just get
the boss on the phone.

662
00:32:33,623 --> 00:32:37,103
A word with you, old chap?

663
00:32:40,117 --> 00:32:42,499
What do you want?

664
00:32:42,500 --> 00:32:46,700
"Today I destroy the villain the same
way the villain destroyed my family".

665
00:32:46,701 --> 00:32:48,432
Yeah. So?

666
00:32:48,433 --> 00:32:52,150
Perhaps there's another code
buried in the message itself.

667
00:32:52,151 --> 00:32:56,549
Daniel, you don't have to listen to him.

668
00:32:56,550 --> 00:32:58,377
Each letter represents a number.

669
00:32:58,378 --> 00:33:00,309
You don't need his help.

670
00:33:00,310 --> 00:33:02,259
Perhaps it's an address.

671
00:33:02,260 --> 00:33:03,943
You've cracked the ciphers.

672
00:33:03,944 --> 00:33:05,645
Now it's about cracking Eddie.

673
00:33:05,646 --> 00:33:08,100
What do you mean?

674
00:33:08,101 --> 00:33:10,768
What did Dafoe do that really hurt him?

675
00:33:10,769 --> 00:33:14,367
Did he take away his
farm, his livelihood..

676
00:33:14,368 --> 00:33:18,388
Or something more important to him?

677
00:33:23,584 --> 00:33:27,124
I love you, Natalie Vincent.

678
00:33:27,627 --> 00:33:29,235
I did it. I.. I solved the riddle.

679
00:33:29,236 --> 00:33:30,986
- I know what Eddie's doing.
- So do we.

680
00:33:30,987 --> 00:33:33,147
Our agents found a truck
bomb full of fertilizer

681
00:33:33,148 --> 00:33:34,795
just outside Dafoe headquarters.

682
00:33:34,796 --> 00:33:37,795
What? No. No, no, no. That's a decoy.

683
00:33:37,796 --> 00:33:40,536
Remember the original message..
"One down, four to go".

684
00:33:40,537 --> 00:33:41,779
That makes five victims.

685
00:33:41,780 --> 00:33:42,760
Now Eddie's telling us..

686
00:33:42,761 --> 00:33:47,154
"Today I destroy the villain the same
way the villain destroyed my family".

687
00:33:47,155 --> 00:33:50,781
H.. His Father's in prison, his Mother
took her own life, all because of Dafoe.

688
00:33:50,782 --> 00:33:54,058
Three of the victims are
dead. Who are the last two?

689
00:33:54,059 --> 00:33:56,759
Dafoe's parents.

690
00:34:01,580 --> 00:34:03,373
He's in there with the Dafoes.

691
00:34:03,374 --> 00:34:05,472
Question is, what's he waiting for?

692
00:34:05,473 --> 00:34:08,942
He's waiting to talk to me.

693
00:34:08,943 --> 00:34:11,021
Want to give this a try?

694
00:34:11,022 --> 00:34:12,482
No, it's got to
be face-to-face.

695
00:34:12,483 --> 00:34:13,878
Daniel, you're not going in there.

696
00:34:13,879 --> 00:34:15,381
He told me how to find him.

697
00:34:15,382 --> 00:34:18,645
He must have something to say to me.

698
00:34:18,646 --> 00:34:21,156
All right, well, I'm going in with you.

699
00:34:21,157 --> 00:34:23,822
And you're wearing a wire so
SWAT can hear what's going on.

700
00:34:23,823 --> 00:34:26,092
Look, if you can get
him in front of a window,

701
00:34:26,093 --> 00:34:30,233
one of my snipers can take him out.

702
00:34:41,789 --> 00:34:43,682
Uh, Eddie..

703
00:34:43,683 --> 00:34:45,787
I'm Dr. Daniel Pierce.

704
00:34:45,788 --> 00:34:48,428
May I come in?

705
00:34:50,618 --> 00:34:52,089
Just him.

706
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:54,450
And if you or anyone else
so much as rattles this

707
00:34:54,451 --> 00:34:56,411
doorknob, I press this button,
and we all go up together.

708
00:34:56,412 --> 00:34:59,232
Do you understand?

709
00:34:59,466 --> 00:35:03,126
- Daniel.
- I.. I can do it.

710
00:35:21,048 --> 00:35:23,784
There's a way out of this, Eddie.

711
00:35:23,785 --> 00:35:26,714
There's no other way out for me.

712
00:35:26,715 --> 00:35:28,808
If you believe that..

713
00:35:28,809 --> 00:35:31,224
Then why did you tell
me where to find you?

714
00:35:31,225 --> 00:35:33,896
I mean, the puzzles were clever but..

715
00:35:33,897 --> 00:35:35,141
You knew I'd be able to solve them.

716
00:35:35,142 --> 00:35:37,013
Yeah. I wanted you here..

717
00:35:37,014 --> 00:35:40,339
Because you said you were my kindred
spirit, and I wanted to believe

718
00:35:40,340 --> 00:35:44,376
that there was someone out
there who understood me.

719
00:35:44,377 --> 00:35:48,021
But you've been working
for the cops the whole time.

720
00:35:48,022 --> 00:35:50,127
You're gonna have to die with me.

721
00:35:50,128 --> 00:35:51,549
Get him out of there right now!

722
00:35:51,550 --> 00:35:53,623
No, if we storm in there,
he pushes the button.

723
00:35:53,624 --> 00:35:57,164
Your guy's all on his own.

724
00:36:00,279 --> 00:36:02,927
You know, I knew I was taking a risk
when I came through that door but uh..

725
00:36:02,928 --> 00:36:06,168
- I came anyway.
- Why?

726
00:36:06,329 --> 00:36:07,584
Because I am your kindred spirit.

727
00:36:07,585 --> 00:36:09,236
- Bullshit.
- No, it's true.

728
00:36:09,237 --> 00:36:10,551
Yeah, I'm working for the cops,

729
00:36:10,552 --> 00:36:14,027
but I believe in what
you're fighting for, Eddie.

730
00:36:14,028 --> 00:36:17,541
I hate lawyers, Eddie, and
.. And.. And corporations

731
00:36:17,542 --> 00:36:21,479
and the way they screw over
hardworking, honest people.

732
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:24,557
What Scantlin and Anderson and the rest
of those bastards did to your family..

733
00:36:24,558 --> 00:36:27,052
Is unforgivable. It's.. It's evil.

734
00:36:27,053 --> 00:36:32,094
I understand why you'd
want to make them pay. I do.

735
00:36:32,095 --> 00:36:36,041
- But these people didn't do anything.
- Yes, they did.

736
00:36:36,042 --> 00:36:38,184
They raised a monster.

737
00:36:38,185 --> 00:36:41,594
They raised a son that
has no conscience at all.

738
00:36:41,595 --> 00:36:45,482
And your Father raised you,
and you do have a conscience.

739
00:36:45,483 --> 00:36:47,850
And that's the real reason that
you brought me here, isn't it?

740
00:36:47,851 --> 00:36:49,810
Because deep down, you
want me to stop you from

741
00:36:49,811 --> 00:36:51,476
- killing anyone else.
- You're wrong.

742
00:36:51,477 --> 00:36:55,815
You started this, Eddie, because you
wanted to make your Father proud of you.

743
00:36:55,816 --> 00:36:58,116
He still can be.

744
00:36:58,117 --> 00:37:01,651
Nobody else has to die. You've
already finished the job.

745
00:37:01,652 --> 00:37:02,831
What are you talking about?

746
00:37:02,832 --> 00:37:06,732
Dafoe and Wei are going to jail.

747
00:37:07,277 --> 00:37:08,256
You're lying.

748
00:37:08,257 --> 00:37:09,374
No, I'm not.

749
00:37:09,375 --> 00:37:11,237
Thanks to you, I figured
out what they were doing

750
00:37:11,238 --> 00:37:13,226
to your Father and the other farmers.

751
00:37:13,227 --> 00:37:16,365
The U.S. Attorney is gonna indict
them. There'll be lawsuits, Eddie.

752
00:37:16,366 --> 00:37:17,963
Some of those farmers
will get their land back.

753
00:37:17,964 --> 00:37:20,254
It's too late for my Father and me.

754
00:37:20,255 --> 00:37:22,340
Well, maybe you could still be together.

755
00:37:22,341 --> 00:37:24,201
How?

756
00:37:24,535 --> 00:37:25,848
In hell?

757
00:37:25,849 --> 00:37:29,717
I'll talk to the U.S. Attorney about
having you sentenced to Stateville.

758
00:37:29,718 --> 00:37:31,998
I promise.

759
00:37:33,475 --> 00:37:35,395
Now..

760
00:37:35,452 --> 00:37:38,739
Why don't you put down
that detonator and..

761
00:37:38,740 --> 00:37:42,048
Let's walk out of here together.

762
00:37:42,049 --> 00:37:47,949
If I go out there, the only cell they're
gonna put me in is one on Death Row.

763
00:37:50,761 --> 00:37:53,881
And I deserve to die.

764
00:37:55,413 --> 00:37:56,984
I killed an innocent girl.

765
00:37:56,985 --> 00:38:00,545
Yeah, and you can pay for that
crime, Eddie, but not with your life.

766
00:38:00,546 --> 00:38:02,147
There were mitigating circumstances.

767
00:38:02,148 --> 00:38:05,303
You were traumatized by what Dafoe
and his cabal did to your family,

768
00:38:05,304 --> 00:38:07,035
and I'll testify to that.

769
00:38:07,036 --> 00:38:10,216
You lied to me before.

770
00:38:10,223 --> 00:38:12,316
How do I know you're
not lying to me now?

771
00:38:12,317 --> 00:38:15,251
I got the shot, Sir. Take it.

772
00:38:15,252 --> 00:38:17,930
Eddie, get away from that window!

773
00:38:17,931 --> 00:38:19,791
God!

774
00:38:27,084 --> 00:38:30,827
Why the hell did you do that, huh?

775
00:38:30,828 --> 00:38:33,362
Why didn't you just let them kill me?

776
00:38:33,363 --> 00:38:36,459
Because I meant what I said, Eddie.

777
00:38:36,460 --> 00:38:39,700
Nobody else has to die.

778
00:38:47,634 --> 00:38:50,610
I could still push this button.

779
00:38:50,611 --> 00:38:53,191
Yeah, you can.

780
00:38:56,302 --> 00:39:00,442
But I don't think you're going to.

781
00:39:14,711 --> 00:39:20,231
Come on. Come on. Come on.
What the hell is going on?

782
00:39:25,008 --> 00:39:28,710
Hold your fire!

783
00:39:28,711 --> 00:39:30,358
He's surrendering!

784
00:39:30,359 --> 00:39:32,037
He left the detonator inside!

785
00:39:32,038 --> 00:39:34,738
Go! Go! Go! Go!

786
00:39:40,271 --> 00:39:44,051
You did the right thing, Eddie.

787
00:39:48,297 --> 00:39:50,234
Daniel!

788
00:39:50,235 --> 00:39:51,991
- Are you okay?
- Yep.

789
00:39:51,992 --> 00:39:53,411
You sure?

790
00:39:53,412 --> 00:39:57,647
Yeah. That.. That could have
gone a whole different way.

791
00:39:57,648 --> 00:40:00,032
I knew you were crazy. I
didn't know you were that crazy.

792
00:40:00,033 --> 00:40:02,793
Yeah. Me neither.

793
00:40:05,790 --> 00:40:08,850
What is a conscience?

794
00:40:10,027 --> 00:40:14,527
Is it something we can locate on an MRI?

795
00:40:14,663 --> 00:40:19,936
Studies have shown that people with damage
to the Ventromedial Prefrontal Cortex

796
00:40:19,937 --> 00:40:23,891
are actually more willing
to sacrifice a human life

797
00:40:23,892 --> 00:40:29,279
as long as they perceive that
it's for some greater good.

798
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:31,201
But what about people
who have no trouble

799
00:40:31,202 --> 00:40:34,662
sacrificing others to
their own selfish ends?

800
00:40:34,663 --> 00:40:37,484
Is heartless cruelty our true nature?

801
00:40:37,485 --> 00:40:40,218
And empathy the aberration?

802
00:40:40,219 --> 00:40:44,384
My Grandmother used to
say, "it's nice to be nice".

803
00:40:44,385 --> 00:40:45,508
And that may be true.

804
00:40:45,509 --> 00:40:51,409
Or are we better off spending every waking
moment tending our own selfish needs?

805
00:40:51,441 --> 00:40:54,506
The good news is, it turns out
there's an evolutionary advantage

806
00:40:54,507 --> 00:40:56,800
to simple human kindness.

807
00:40:56,801 --> 00:41:01,605
We couldn't get through a cold paleolithic
winter without a little cooperation.

808
00:41:01,606 --> 00:41:06,485
Still, on some prehistoric
level we're all lone hunters.

809
00:41:06,486 --> 00:41:12,386
So it can feel dangerous to show any
softness to other members of the tribe.

810
00:41:16,739 --> 00:41:21,254
But if we manage to lay down our
clubs and our sharpened rocks,

811
00:41:21,255 --> 00:41:25,476
answering the call of the
altruistic imperative..

812
00:41:25,477 --> 00:41:28,657
Can be its own reward.

